NAME
----
xe-host-reboot - Reboot a XenServer host

SYNOPSIS
--------
*xe host-reboot* [ host-selectors ] [--multiple]

DESCRIPTION
-----------
*xe host-reboot* reboots specified disabled XenServer host(s). Use *xe host-disable* to disable a XenServer host. Currently running Virtual Machines that are a resident on rebooting hosts will be evacuated, and migrated to available hosts. After the rebooting hosts have completed the reboot, they will reconnect and synchronize with the pool.


REQUIRED PARAMETERS
-------------------
<host-selectors>::
	Parameters to select host(s) - Use *xe host-list params=all* to get a list of host parameters to filter on. 
	
OPTIONAL PARAMETERS
-------------------
*--multiple*::
	Specify --multiple if you want to match more than one host.
	
EXAMPLES
--------
To reboot a host using a UUID:

- *xe host-reboot* uuid=<HOST UUID>

